article.description: — Troy D'Amico scored all 17 of his points in the second half to spark Southern Illinois to a 65-53 victory over Evansville on Sunday.
article.headline: D'Amico scores 17, sparks Southern Illinois past Evansville 65-53
article.linkText: D'Amico scores 17, sparks Southern Illinois past Evansville 65-53
article.story: EVANSVILLE, Ind. -- — Troy D'Amico scored all 17 of his points in the second half to spark Southern Illinois to a 65-53 victory over Evansville on Sunday. D'Amico also snagged six rebounds for the Salukis (19-10, 11-7 Missouri Valley Conference). Xavier Johnson finished with 12 points, 10 rebounds and eight assists. Scottie Ebube hit two 3-pointers and scored 12. The Purple Aces (15-14, 6-12) were led by Ben Humrichous' 11 points and seven rebounds. Antonio Thomas had 10 points and Tanner Cuff scored nine. Evansville led 26-24 at halftime, but D'Amico took over after intermission to deliver the victory. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
